 at the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../093/1081093.xml">
IMG Soccer Academy</link> in Bradenton, FL.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref><p>

Pareja came up through the youth system of <link>
Atlético Nacional</link>; however, he began his professional career in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../760/34760.xml">
1987</link>, debuting for renowned club <link>
Independiente Medellín</link>, and assisted on the winning goal in a 1-0 victory on his debut.  He played eight years with Independient Medellín, from 1987 to <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../658/34658.xml">
1995</link>, helping them to be runners-up in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../598/34598.xml">
1993</link>, and leading them to a respectable performance in the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../337/18948337.xml">
1994</link> <event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
